  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/66090537" />
    <a title="britt_brooke" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1136632-britt-brooke"><img alt="britt_brooke" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617240715p2/1136632.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/66090537?book_show_action=true">Aug 03, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="britt_brooke" class="user" itemprop="url" name="britt_brooke" href="/user/show/1136632-britt-brooke">britt_brooke</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1136632-britt-brooke?shelf=memoir-biography">memoir-biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1136632-britt-brooke?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1136632-britt-brooke?shelf=essays-short-stories">essays-short-stories</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer66090537" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13335783129623066859">A reread sparked by my dear Meg! I think this is the only Sedaris I hadn’t read multiple times 🤔 - that is, aside from Squirrel Meets Chipmunk which was a bit of a fiasco, IMO. As always, his personal essays are the right mix of wit, dark humor, and self deprecation. Absolutely one of my top authors! And van Gogh’s “Skull with Burning Cigarette” is a favorite painting AND book cover. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


